Imho, Chinese is a @(#$*&amp; of alot tougher than Korean to learn.  Chinese grammar has a tiny similarity to English's, but the language is saddled with all-kanji, 24-7... and, as The Horse points out, Korean pronunciation is waaay simple, but Chinese has those tonal intonations (think of bridge-hashi vs. chopsticks-hashi) on every frikkin' syllable, plus some consonant sounds that you've NEVER heard b4 !<br>
